<subSubSection pageId="73" pageNumber="74" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
Based on external characters, no close relatives were recovered in the phylogenetic analysis of morphological characters by 
<bibRefCitation pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
Reemer and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="StÃ¥hls">Stahls</normalizedToken>
(in press)
</bibRefCitation>
. The species is characterized by its metallic blue colouration and golden pilosity, a long basoflagellomere, a medially widely bare face, a rectangular postero-apical corner of wing cell r4+5, and unfused tergites 3 and 4. The latter character may indicate affinity with 
<taxonomicName authority="Wiedemann, 1824" authorityName="Wiedemann" authorityYear="1824" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ceratophya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ceratophya" order="Diptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ceratophya</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hull, 1944" authorityName="Hull" authorityYear="1944" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Kryptopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Kryptopyga" order="Diptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Kryptopyga</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authority="Reemer, 2013" authorityName="Reemer" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Thompsodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Thompsodon" order="Diptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Thompsodon</taxonomicName>
, but the species lacks other diagnostic characters for these taxa. This species is left unplaced for now.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
